   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23130_WScott_to_ME_letter01_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                     My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               Your letter has just acquainted<lb/>
               us that we are to be deprived of the pleasure of<lb/>
               making your personal acquaintance so much<lb/>
               desired till Friday when we shall claim you &amp;<lb/>
               the young ladies - I am this instant arrived from<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Abbotsford-House_STK">Abbotsford</placeName> where I have been busier than ever was<lb/>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Ormon1">King <choice><orig>Corney</orig><reg>Corny</reg></choice> and in the same fantastic sort of <choice><orig>labours</orig><reg>labors</reg></choice><lb/>
               in which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Willi1">his Majesty</persName> was pleased to delight.</title><lb/>
               I have just his to add kind respects to<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StewD1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StewH1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Stuart</persName> &amp; to assure you that I am<lb/>
               Most sincerely &amp; respectfully<lb/>
               yours<lb/>
               Wednesday<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW1"><hi rend="underline">Walter Scott</hi></persName><lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edinburgh_STK"><choice><orig>Edin<hi rend="superscript">h</hi></orig><reg>Edinburgh</reg></choice></placeName> -<lb/>
               On Saturday a sort of Shoemakers holiday with me I<lb/>
               propose if the weather be favourable going to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Roslin_STK">Roslin</placeName><lb/>
               strangely enough my girls have never seen I <choice><orig>ex<lb/>
               pect</orig><reg>expect</reg></choice><lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23130_WScott_to_ME_letter01_page02.jpg"/>
               just much pleasures from <choice><orig>shewing</orig><reg>showing</reg></choice> you the banks of<lb/>
               the Eske - long my favourite strolling ground -<lb/>
               <note type="bottom"><persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW1">Sir Walter</persName><lb/>
               May 1823<lb/></note>
            </p>
         </div>
